OL,3,CPoll suggests growing fear among
OL,4,CMuslim women in the UK
OL,6,FAlmost half of British Muslim women
OL,7,Ffeel less safe than they did a year
OL,8,Fago, blaming a rise in Islamophobia,
OL,9,Faccording to a new poll.
OL,11,FResearch carried out by pollsters
OL,12,FSurvation found that 30% of Muslim
OL,13,Frespondents said they did not feel
OL,14,Fsafe going out at night, while more
OL,15,Fthan half said politicians in the UK
OL,16,Fhad made them feel less welcome.
OL,18,FHina Khan, 27, told ITV News she
OL,19,Fregularly encounters Islamophobia
OL,20,Fonline, including accusations that she
OL,21,Fsupports extremism.
