OL,6,FThe Londoner said the experience has
OL,7,Fmade her feel unwelcome in the UK.
OL,9,F"'I will never understand how this
OL,10,Fkind of hatred can exist in the
OL,11,Fworld,'" she said.
OL,13,F"You have to shut yourself off from
OL,14,Fit, and build a kind of wall to
OL,15,Fseparate the emotion from the facts.
OL,16,FBut even with that wall up, it still
OL,17,Fchips away at you. Over time, it makes
OL,18,Fyou feel small. You start to question
OL,19,Fhow safe you really are in this
OL,20,Fcountry ` or whether you truly belong
OL,21,Fhere.
