OL,6,F"Our charity has also felt the brunt
OL,7,Fof a worrying rise in Islamophobia
OL,8,Fonline, and particularly across social
OL,9,Fmedia. People increasingly feel they
OL,10,Fcan post malicious and hateful content
OL,11,Fwithout any consequences," Mr Hussain
OL,12,Fsaid.
OL,14,F"Social media has become a dangerous
OL,15,Fspace for false news in which
OL,16,Forganisations such as Islamic Relief,
OL,17,Fwho are committed to helping and
OL,18,Fsaving people's lives across the world
OL,19,Fincluding the UK, are instead
OL,20,Fsubjected to hateful abuse.
